WEBVTT

00:14.639 --> 00:16.599
[woman on phone]
<i>Make peace with yourself.</i>

00:17.642 --> 00:21.271
<i>Make peace with</i>
<i>the amazing person that you truly are.</i>

00:22.772 --> 00:25.316
<i>Your mind is your greatest asset.</i>

00:26.359 --> 00:28.778
<i>You are your own best tool.</i>

00:29.612 --> 00:31.364
["Strut" playing]

00:46.379 --> 00:49.674
<i>♪ He said</i>
<i>"Baby, what's wrong with you?" ♪</i>

00:49.758 --> 00:54.721
♪ <i>"Why can't you use your imagination?"</i>
<i>Oh, no, oh, no ♪</i>

00:54.804 --> 00:57.849
♪ <i>Standing in the half light</i>
<i>You're almost like her ♪</i>

00:57.932 --> 01:02.604
♪ <i>Huh, take it slow</i>
<i>Like your daddy told you ♪</i>

01:02.687 --> 01:07.233
♪ <i>Strut, pout, put it out</i>
<i>That's what you want from women ♪</i>

01:07.317 --> 01:11.488
♪ <i>Come on, baby, what you taking me for? ♪</i>

01:11.571 --> 01:13.073
♪ <i>Strut, pout, cut it out ♪</i>

01:13.156 --> 01:15.742
♪ <i>All taking and no giving ♪</i>

01:15.825 --> 01:20.038
♪ <i>Watch me, baby</i>
<i>While I walk out the door ♪</i>

01:24.918 --> 01:26.753
I am my own best tool.

01:36.429 --> 01:40.767
♪ <i>Strut, pout, put it out</i>
<i>That's what you want from women ♪</i>

01:41.726 --> 01:43.645
-[song stops]
-[Annie] Be cool.

01:44.604 --> 01:45.480
[thuds]

01:54.864 --> 01:55.782
[zipper closing]

02:06.042 --> 02:07.752
[Ben] Why are you in clothes?

02:10.046 --> 02:11.297
Why are you awake?

02:11.381 --> 02:12.549
I have practice.

02:12.632 --> 02:13.716
Before school?

02:14.509 --> 02:15.885
Can't do it in school.

02:17.053 --> 02:18.471
But it's extracurricular.

02:18.555 --> 02:20.098
Yeah, extra.

02:22.600 --> 02:23.518
Hmm.

02:24.435 --> 02:25.770
What's your excuse?

02:26.479 --> 02:27.313
Work.

02:27.814 --> 02:29.649
You got home, like, three hours ago.

02:30.692 --> 02:32.360
I forgot to lock up.

02:33.403 --> 02:34.821
Store's open 24 hours.

02:38.283 --> 02:39.450
What's in the backpack?

02:40.451 --> 02:42.579
-Mostly tampons.
-Can I see?

02:43.454 --> 02:44.914
-You know what's so weird?
-Guns?

02:44.998 --> 02:46.916
-You didn't go to bed a cop…
-Drugs?

02:47.000 --> 02:48.626
-…but you woke up one.
-Body parts?

02:49.335 --> 02:51.588
Remind me never to get up early again.

02:56.301 --> 02:59.304
All right. Be on your way.

03:02.015 --> 03:03.349
I will bring you a Slurpee.

03:03.433 --> 03:05.143
If only you were going to work.

03:06.019 --> 03:06.936
[Annie sighs]

03:07.937 --> 03:08.938
[sighs]

03:09.022 --> 03:10.356
[teacher] You're not dumb.

03:12.609 --> 03:13.443
[exhales sharply]

03:13.526 --> 03:15.737
[teacher] You just weren't prepared.

03:16.529 --> 03:17.739
So, let's try again.

03:17.822 --> 03:21.200
If you can open up
your textbooks to chapter six, page 89.

03:23.703 --> 03:25.622
Will you take me to Annabelle's?

03:26.289 --> 03:27.290
[sighs]

03:29.167 --> 03:30.460
Can your mom take you?

03:30.543 --> 03:31.753
I want you.

03:31.836 --> 03:34.714
-Can she come over here?
-She has better dolls.

03:36.299 --> 03:37.634
What about FaceTime?

03:38.384 --> 03:39.594
Not the same.

03:40.762 --> 03:45.058
What if you
rode your scooter over to her house?

03:45.683 --> 03:48.478
I can't cross the street by myself.

03:48.561 --> 03:50.480
[sighs] Well, maybe it's time.

03:51.731 --> 03:53.358
Hey. Go get your shoes, sweetie.

03:54.150 --> 03:56.110
-But I want Dad.
-Go.

03:59.906 --> 04:01.115
How long does that take?

04:02.492 --> 04:03.534
[Dean] When it beeps.

04:03.618 --> 04:05.119
Do you want a pillow or something?

04:05.203 --> 04:06.329
How did you get it?

04:06.955 --> 04:08.998
-What?
-The bail.

04:11.668 --> 04:13.127
I mean… [scoffs]

04:13.211 --> 04:15.588
We were drowning
before they even took the shop.

04:16.297 --> 04:17.507
Come here, sit up.

04:27.600 --> 04:29.435
What did he make you do this time?

04:31.229 --> 04:32.146
It's not him.

04:33.648 --> 04:34.524
Who is it?

04:35.233 --> 04:36.276
Does it matter?

04:36.359 --> 04:38.319
[scoffs] Yeah, kind of.

04:38.403 --> 04:39.988
Would you rather just go back?

04:40.780 --> 04:41.781
[sighs]

04:41.864 --> 04:44.158
-[scoffs]
-[ankle monitor beeping]

04:44.242 --> 04:45.535
I'll take Jane.

04:45.618 --> 04:46.744
[continues beeping]

04:55.837 --> 04:56.838
[indistinct chatter]

04:57.839 --> 04:59.215
[upbeat music playing]

05:24.157 --> 05:26.492
-We out of peanut butter?
-We are.

05:29.370 --> 05:30.413
We out of bread, too?

05:31.164 --> 05:32.457
You see any bread?

05:32.540 --> 05:33.416
No.

05:33.499 --> 05:35.251
Then you have your answer.

05:38.129 --> 05:40.381
-Can you go to the store?
-Sure.

05:41.049 --> 05:43.176
As soon as we stop showering,

05:44.510 --> 05:46.220
stop watching TV…

05:47.263 --> 05:48.389
and stop cooking.

05:48.473 --> 05:49.307
[sighs]

05:50.058 --> 05:52.143
[Stan] Got it. How bad?

05:53.186 --> 05:56.355
As long as you don't need to
see the food we can't buy or cook,

05:56.439 --> 05:58.191
we can probably keep the TV going.

05:58.274 --> 06:00.735
[sighs] Well, that's okay, 'cause…

06:01.778 --> 06:04.197
I got a craving for saltines and mustard.

06:06.657 --> 06:08.493
You cannot be serious.

06:08.576 --> 06:10.703
I could do Cheerios and barbeque sauce.

06:10.787 --> 06:12.163
Her meds went up again.

06:14.123 --> 06:15.124
They just upped them.

06:15.208 --> 06:17.543
-And they upped the up.
-How much?

06:22.381 --> 06:23.674
What are we gonna do?

06:26.969 --> 06:28.471
I know this is kinda my fault.

06:28.554 --> 06:29.639
All your fault.

06:29.722 --> 06:32.975
And I don't want to make things
any worse than I already have.

06:33.935 --> 06:36.020
But you just can't help yourself.

06:37.730 --> 06:40.733
-What's going on with the bags?
-What do you mean?

06:41.943 --> 06:45.571
Maybe you can ask for
some kind of commission or something.

06:46.280 --> 06:47.657
This isn't Herbalife, babe.

06:47.740 --> 06:49.200
But you made the deal.

06:49.867 --> 06:50.743
To stay alive.

06:51.661 --> 06:52.745
Well, are they selling?

06:52.829 --> 06:56.582
I don't know, Ruby. He's got 'em
in some car washes around town.

06:56.666 --> 06:58.209
Car washes?

06:58.292 --> 06:59.710
Some gas stations, too.

06:59.794 --> 07:02.505
They're fake Celines, not Slim Jims.

07:03.798 --> 07:05.550
It's gonna be a condiment kinda month.

07:05.633 --> 07:07.343
Got to do better than that.

07:08.344 --> 07:09.887
Then get it from your guy.

07:14.183 --> 07:15.017
[sighs]

07:15.101 --> 07:17.061
[Beth] <i>He just won't wash right now.</i>

07:17.145 --> 07:18.646
And we can't live without our cut.

07:18.729 --> 07:20.731
How is that my problem?

07:20.815 --> 07:23.818
-This takes up all of our time.
-I can barely work.

07:23.901 --> 07:26.195
It's not like
we're ratting out pencil pushers.

07:26.279 --> 07:29.073
There's crime. Undercover crime.

07:29.157 --> 07:31.868
-These fools are packing, yo.
-None of it pays anymore.

07:34.245 --> 07:36.497
We're not your financial planners.

07:37.582 --> 07:40.168
-Could we get an advance or something?
-On what?

07:40.251 --> 07:42.503
-On our salary.
-What salary?

07:42.587 --> 07:44.172
The one we'll get in our new lives.

07:44.255 --> 07:46.007
You don't have new lives yet.

07:46.090 --> 07:48.217
But we can't afford our old ones.

07:48.301 --> 07:49.760
I can't even pay my rent.

07:49.844 --> 07:51.471
Hey, guess where you won't have to.

07:52.054 --> 07:55.433
-[Annie scoffs]
-When… do you meet the boss?

07:56.517 --> 07:58.895
Oh, I'm still waiting on my e-vite.

08:11.908 --> 08:13.117
I like your eyes.

08:13.910 --> 08:16.162
-Excuse me?
-The smoky stuff.

08:17.538 --> 08:19.874
-My makeup?
-What's it called?

08:23.419 --> 08:24.295
Eye shadow.

08:26.005 --> 08:28.925
Would you say it's, like, slate
or more of a smoky grey?

08:30.301 --> 08:31.719
She'll text you a link.

08:32.929 --> 08:33.930
Mmm.

08:41.687 --> 08:42.522
[sighs]

08:53.741 --> 08:54.909
Hey, mama.

08:56.744 --> 08:58.412
I can trust you, right? [echoing]

09:07.046 --> 09:08.130
[children laughing]

09:14.887 --> 09:16.180
Follow the money.

09:18.849 --> 09:20.560
What color lip gloss is that?

09:22.937 --> 09:24.730
Boss will know where it goes.

09:28.192 --> 09:30.111
My people want to check you out. [echoing]

09:30.194 --> 09:31.279
[continues cutting]

09:45.459 --> 09:46.836
You got this, girl.

09:47.503 --> 09:48.921
We're counting on you.

09:49.839 --> 09:52.717
Don't let me down. All right?

09:52.800 --> 09:53.843
[breathing heavily]

09:56.887 --> 09:58.556
Do you have a USB cable?

09:58.639 --> 10:01.225
This thing is flashing.
I need to charge it.

10:02.393 --> 10:03.769
Yeah, it's in my purse.

10:05.438 --> 10:06.397
Okay.

10:08.274 --> 10:09.358
[cell phone chimes]

10:25.249 --> 10:27.960
[Ruby] What happens
when his boss has a boss?

10:28.044 --> 10:29.795
And that boss has a boss?

10:29.879 --> 10:31.547
[Ruby] We work harder and harder.

10:31.631 --> 10:33.591
And get poorer and poorer.

10:33.674 --> 10:36.177
And still end up deader and deader.

10:36.260 --> 10:37.261
And deader.

10:38.929 --> 10:40.598
Because there's three of us.

10:42.183 --> 10:43.184
Hello?

10:44.560 --> 10:45.645
Yo, Holly Hobbie.

10:45.728 --> 10:47.938
Anything at all to contribute?

10:48.856 --> 10:49.940
What do we do?

10:53.819 --> 10:55.780
Green or orange around the mouth?

11:04.372 --> 11:06.165
[Dave] Hey, give me that blue aux.

11:08.459 --> 11:10.378
-Do you feel that?
-Hmm.

11:10.461 --> 11:13.172
[gasps] The rush.

11:14.048 --> 11:15.257
From the fumes?

11:15.841 --> 11:18.761
-Here. You try. This one goes right there.
-Okay.

11:18.844 --> 11:22.181
How awesome is it being in the field?

11:22.264 --> 11:23.224
Hmm.

11:24.266 --> 11:28.104
-Food's better than the cafeteria.
-How about no D-bag suits to report to?

11:28.187 --> 11:29.522
-Sounds nice.
-Right?

11:29.605 --> 11:30.439
For you.

11:32.274 --> 11:35.778
Point is,
if we deliver on this, everything changes.

11:35.861 --> 11:37.238
-Really?
-Yeah, yeah.

11:37.321 --> 11:39.073
Could mean Division Chief.

11:39.657 --> 11:41.951
-For me, too?
-If you play your cards right.

11:42.034 --> 11:42.993
Hmm.

11:44.495 --> 11:47.415
-What did you do to your face?
-Nothing.

11:48.040 --> 11:49.542
Yeah. Is that eye shadow?

11:50.459 --> 11:51.335
No.

11:53.212 --> 11:54.964
Oh… [sighs]

11:56.090 --> 11:57.091
Listen, I…

11:58.050 --> 12:01.595
I worked with this CI once. Great guy.

12:01.679 --> 12:03.013
Loved Kenny Chesney.

12:03.097 --> 12:05.307
We'd go out, we'd get sauced.

12:05.391 --> 12:07.226
-Fun.
-He even taught me to line dance.

12:07.309 --> 12:09.103
You've got to make them trust you.

12:09.186 --> 12:10.938
Problem was, I trusted him.

12:13.023 --> 12:14.942
I'm not going dancing with her.

12:15.609 --> 12:17.111
They're not your friends.

12:17.194 --> 12:18.863
I just had to find my way in.

12:18.946 --> 12:21.866
Only reason she's
talking to you is because we caught her.

12:25.286 --> 12:27.079
What happened with your Chesney pal?

12:27.163 --> 12:30.166
He played me like a steel guitar.

12:30.249 --> 12:31.625
They shut down the whole op.

12:31.709 --> 12:32.751
I get it.

12:32.835 --> 12:34.920
[sighs] Took 15 years
to dig out of that hole.

12:35.671 --> 12:37.339
I'm gonna make her my bitch, okay?

12:39.091 --> 12:42.553
Just don't forget
what's pretend… and what's real.

12:46.348 --> 12:47.933
Not your color, by the way.

12:59.945 --> 13:01.822
-[Tyler] Your place is really nice.
-Oh.

13:01.906 --> 13:04.408
Thanks. You've been here before, right?

13:05.242 --> 13:07.077
Just to help you move your couch.

13:07.786 --> 13:09.330
What about my Super Bowl party?

13:10.581 --> 13:11.999
I wasn't invited.

13:12.583 --> 13:13.417
To any of them?

13:13.501 --> 13:14.960
Wait, there was more than one?

13:17.004 --> 13:20.132
Let's talk a little bit more
about you, Baby T. What's new?

13:23.260 --> 13:24.595
I rescued a cat.

13:25.262 --> 13:27.014
-Aw!
-And he drowned himself.

13:27.681 --> 13:28.557
Aw…

13:28.641 --> 13:33.562
So, tell me a little bit more
about this exciting new job of yours.

13:33.646 --> 13:35.272
It's not really that exciting.

13:36.106 --> 13:37.191
What if…

13:40.611 --> 13:41.946
What if it could be?

13:49.662 --> 13:51.872
["Objet Petit A" playing]

13:58.170 --> 13:59.922
It's a new place in Grosse Pointe.

14:00.714 --> 14:02.299
It's a lot of eyes.

14:02.841 --> 14:04.051
It's only one exit.

14:04.134 --> 14:06.220
Police station right down the road.

14:06.804 --> 14:07.805
[Dean] Hey, ladies.

14:09.390 --> 14:10.432
[sighs]

14:10.516 --> 14:13.143
Hey, have you seen my, um, Allen wrenches?

14:14.895 --> 14:16.605
-No.
-[drawer opens]

14:16.689 --> 14:17.773
[objects clattering]

14:27.032 --> 14:28.868
[Annie] Different key for each case.

14:31.453 --> 14:33.080
It'll take forever.

14:34.039 --> 14:35.165
Suicide mission.

14:38.419 --> 14:39.336
Perfect.

14:44.341 --> 14:45.926
♪ <i>I heard you said ♪</i>

14:47.052 --> 14:48.429
♪ <i>I heard how you said it ♪</i>

14:49.722 --> 14:51.056
♪ <i>You heard what I said ♪</i>

14:52.266 --> 14:53.851
♪ <i>You heard how I said it ♪</i>

14:55.019 --> 14:56.312
♪ <i>I'm not afraid ♪</i>

14:57.479 --> 14:59.982
♪ <i>Just take one of your wires ♪</i>

15:00.065 --> 15:01.942
♪ <i>It's not heavy enough ♪</i>

15:02.651 --> 15:04.194
♪ <i>Unless you open your eyes ♪</i>

15:05.863 --> 15:07.031
[song continues in French]

15:26.800 --> 15:28.510
♪ <i>I've been crashing ♪</i>

15:29.678 --> 15:31.055
♪ <i>Almost every night ♪</i>

15:31.972 --> 15:36.477
♪ <i>But it pains me to see</i>
<i>I'm not even bruised ♪</i>

15:37.728 --> 15:40.689
<i>♪ Just gonna stay up</i>
<i>To the touch ♪</i>

15:40.773 --> 15:43.150
♪ <i>I radiate heat ♪</i>

15:43.233 --> 15:46.111
♪ <i>Too much mascara ♪</i>

15:46.195 --> 15:48.530
♪ <i>Quick, quick, quick, quick ♪</i>

15:53.118 --> 15:53.953
[Annie] <i>All right!</i>

15:54.036 --> 15:56.622
Everybody be cool, and nobody gets hurt!

15:57.164 --> 15:59.249
["How Do I Live?" playing over speakers]

16:00.834 --> 16:01.961
[Ruby] Time!

16:02.878 --> 16:04.004
[Beth] One minute.

16:05.089 --> 16:07.675
Miss? That one's not locked.

16:07.758 --> 16:10.094
[Beth] Oh, terrific, thank you.

16:11.178 --> 16:12.096
[Annie] Time!

16:13.013 --> 16:14.640
-Come on, pick up the pace!
-[man] Mmm…

16:15.516 --> 16:17.226
-[Beth] Ten seconds.
-[Annie sighs]

16:18.686 --> 16:19.979
[Ruby] Where is this fool?

16:20.062 --> 16:20.938
[Annie] He's coming.

16:22.731 --> 16:23.857
[Beth] That's time.

16:24.817 --> 16:25.985
Everything's insured.

16:27.778 --> 16:29.113
You can go.

16:29.196 --> 16:30.280
[Beth] Um, we will.

16:32.533 --> 16:35.661
-After you open something else.
-You took everything.

16:39.498 --> 16:40.582
[Ruby] Don't look at us.

16:40.666 --> 16:41.917
I haven't called the cops yet.

16:42.001 --> 16:44.461
-[Annie] Get down on the ground!
-Okay.

16:44.545 --> 16:45.587
[Beth sighs]

16:45.671 --> 16:46.714
[Annie clears throat]

16:47.297 --> 16:49.133
-[sighs]
-Where is he?

16:49.216 --> 16:52.636
<i>♪ …ever, ever survive? ♪</i>

16:54.013 --> 16:55.222
You stay down there.

16:55.305 --> 16:58.142
<i>♪ How do I, how do I… ♪</i>

16:58.559 --> 16:59.393
[door opens]

17:02.187 --> 17:03.272
[Annie] Be cool.

17:04.398 --> 17:05.232
[thuds]

17:06.150 --> 17:09.570
<i>♪ There'd be no sun in my sky ♪</i>

17:09.653 --> 17:13.365
<i>♪ There would be no love in my life ♪</i>

17:13.449 --> 17:16.952
<i>♪ There'd be no world left for me ♪</i>

17:17.036 --> 17:20.456
<i>♪ And I ♪</i>

17:21.040 --> 17:22.332
<i>♪ Baby I don't know… ♪</i>

17:22.416 --> 17:23.625
Turn around.

17:24.752 --> 17:26.003
-That way.
-[Beth sighs]

17:26.086 --> 17:31.300
<i>♪ I'd be lost if I lost you</i>
<i>If you ever leave… ♪</i>

17:33.385 --> 17:34.511
Donuts?

17:35.304 --> 17:36.972
I thought it was tomorrow.

17:38.807 --> 17:39.892
[Annie sighs]

17:46.231 --> 17:47.066
Really?

17:48.901 --> 17:50.652
[Dave] What the hell is going on?

17:51.820 --> 17:53.655
Just trying to make a living.

17:53.739 --> 17:55.324
Armed robbery's five to ten.

17:55.407 --> 17:56.533
For squirt guns?

17:57.534 --> 17:58.952
Doesn't matter, actually.

17:59.036 --> 18:00.829
It does when you pull the trigger.

18:02.039 --> 18:03.207
You think this is funny?

18:03.290 --> 18:06.335
-At least here we get three square meals.
-A roof over our head.

18:06.418 --> 18:08.420
-Cute jumpers.
-Ugh, I love orange.

18:08.504 --> 18:09.671
They do blue here.

18:09.755 --> 18:11.757
-Ah, even better.
-[Dave] Fine.

18:12.925 --> 18:14.384
You can all rot.

18:14.468 --> 18:16.303
We'll round up your husband, too.

18:16.386 --> 18:18.055
But how will we finish the job?

18:18.138 --> 18:20.641
You didn't really
give us anything, anyway.

18:20.724 --> 18:23.602
Can you just ask
the security guard for my phone?

18:25.646 --> 18:27.940
I hate when people
don't respond to an e-vite.

18:28.816 --> 18:30.943
Did gang friend actually send an e-vite?

18:32.444 --> 18:33.654
Paperless Post.

18:36.448 --> 18:37.616
When's the meeting?

18:37.699 --> 18:38.909
Does it matter?

18:40.953 --> 18:42.704
You know, I think it actually kinda does.

18:42.788 --> 18:45.582
'Cause if they bail us out,
which they're leaning towards,

18:45.666 --> 18:48.752
then we could
hit that credit union before it closes.

18:48.836 --> 18:51.213
-Uh, it's right next to Walmart.
-Two-fer.

18:51.296 --> 18:53.549
Might want to
hang tight in the parking lot.

18:53.632 --> 18:55.676
We'll probably
be back here before that meeting.

18:57.803 --> 18:59.304
We'll put you on payroll.

18:59.388 --> 19:00.889
Same amount as our cut.

19:01.640 --> 19:02.808
Not happening.

19:02.891 --> 19:03.725
Hmm…

19:04.309 --> 19:06.311
Never knocked over a casino.

19:07.396 --> 19:08.355
Open all night.

19:08.438 --> 19:10.399
-Loaded with cash.
-And on every corner.

19:10.482 --> 19:12.693
-How did we not think of this before?
-I just did.

19:12.776 --> 19:13.819
[chuckles]

19:21.201 --> 19:22.411
[door opens]

19:23.871 --> 19:24.955
[grunts]

19:26.373 --> 19:27.332
Come here.

19:33.505 --> 19:34.798
Your guy came through?

19:35.799 --> 19:36.717
You tell me.

19:37.384 --> 19:38.385
[Stan] Hmm?

19:41.555 --> 19:43.015
Real or fake?

19:44.266 --> 19:46.768
-As long as it pays the bills.
-Come on.

19:48.812 --> 19:50.314
[breathes deeply] Real.

19:53.775 --> 19:54.610
Fake?

19:59.031 --> 20:00.741
I can't tell the difference.

20:00.824 --> 20:01.909
That's the point.

20:05.996 --> 20:07.915
What's that got to do with it?

20:07.998 --> 20:10.459
-You want a cut or not?
-You know it.

20:10.542 --> 20:13.462
Then we've got to show
your guy how valuable you are.

20:16.131 --> 20:18.175
It's missing the engraved logo.

20:19.551 --> 20:20.719
Right here.

20:21.470 --> 20:22.471
In the corner.

20:23.013 --> 20:26.099
Can't sleep on the stitching.
At least ten stitches per inch.

20:26.683 --> 20:28.810
Got to be symmetrical on all sides.

20:30.103 --> 20:31.521
And the real ones…

20:33.607 --> 20:35.234
come with a dust bag.

20:35.943 --> 20:36.944
What's that?

20:37.486 --> 20:38.946
It's like a bag for your bag.

20:39.780 --> 20:41.114
Seems like a waste.

20:42.324 --> 20:43.367
Ladies love it.

20:46.954 --> 20:48.830
Why are you telling me all this?

20:49.790 --> 20:53.001
Because, Gene,
you're selling fake for fake.

20:53.085 --> 20:53.961
So?

20:54.044 --> 20:57.172
Convince women these are real,
you get ten times the money.

21:10.352 --> 21:13.480
All this time, I thought I hired a badass.

21:17.150 --> 21:19.987
Lucky for me, I got a prissy fashionista.

21:21.822 --> 21:23.115
[chuckles]

21:28.328 --> 21:30.372
I really need to pass.

21:33.166 --> 21:36.628
It's not just for me.
It's… It's for my son.

21:37.379 --> 21:42.634
Look, I know this might not seem
like the most important thing in the world

21:42.718 --> 21:44.261
to someone else, but…

21:45.095 --> 21:50.559
I literally cannot
move on with my life without it. So…

21:52.561 --> 21:55.480
if there is anything else…

21:57.316 --> 21:58.442
that I can do…

22:02.738 --> 22:04.448
There's one thing you can do.

22:05.198 --> 22:06.116
Name it.

22:06.992 --> 22:08.201
Take your seat.

22:09.536 --> 22:10.412
S…

22:21.423 --> 22:22.299
[sighs]

22:28.096 --> 22:29.097
How many times?

22:29.973 --> 22:30.974
[speaks Japanese]

22:32.851 --> 22:34.311
[in English] Yeah. Same here.

22:35.353 --> 22:37.981
[teacher] You have seven hours
to complete the test.

22:38.065 --> 22:40.817
First section has a limit of 75 minutes.

22:40.901 --> 22:43.361
I'll notify you
when there's five minutes remaining.

22:43.445 --> 22:46.239
When time's up,
please place your pencils down.

22:46.323 --> 22:47.741
Are there any questions?

22:58.085 --> 22:59.377
[Beth] Get them curry.

22:59.461 --> 23:00.420
Curry?

23:01.296 --> 23:04.049
-Yeah. Jane's learning cultures.
-Okay.

23:04.132 --> 23:05.550
She likes India.

23:06.176 --> 23:08.386
Is the store paying you in cash now?

23:15.143 --> 23:18.063
Remember when you first
went to work for your dad?

23:18.146 --> 23:20.357
You said,
"It's only gonna be for the summer."

23:20.440 --> 23:22.359
Yeah. Stuck for life.

23:23.026 --> 23:24.069
Me, too.

23:24.861 --> 23:26.238
-Let me help.
-Just leave it.

23:26.321 --> 23:27.656
-I got it.
-Leave it.

23:32.786 --> 23:33.703
You okay?

23:46.758 --> 23:48.510
Kenny likes the naan.

23:48.593 --> 23:49.928
It's just flatbread.

23:55.684 --> 23:56.977
<i>What if he checks me?</i>

23:58.186 --> 23:59.020
Improvise.

23:59.104 --> 24:00.605
What if he finds it?

24:00.689 --> 24:01.940
Improvise.

24:02.023 --> 24:03.441
He'd have to get you naked.

24:20.625 --> 24:21.543
[Rio] Hey, now.

24:29.092 --> 24:30.010
Come on.

24:39.436 --> 24:41.229
Do you need to frisk me or something?

24:41.771 --> 24:43.023
[Rio] Nah, you're good.

24:44.900 --> 24:46.318
Don't sweat it, all right?

24:51.281 --> 24:52.407
[children playing]

24:57.495 --> 24:58.788
[Rio] This is my boss.

25:00.123 --> 25:01.875
I'm just his grandmother.

25:01.958 --> 25:02.876
[indistinct chatter]

25:08.173 --> 25:09.174
[chuckles]

25:14.971 --> 25:15.847
[Annie grunts]

25:16.806 --> 25:17.766
[sighs]

25:20.518 --> 25:21.561
[grunts]

25:22.354 --> 25:25.941
[sighs] Come on, creepy guy in 4A.
Why is your Wi-Fi so weak?

25:26.024 --> 25:27.692
-[typing]
-Yes!

25:28.401 --> 25:29.236
[beeps]

25:29.319 --> 25:30.946
No!

25:31.571 --> 25:33.198
-[sighs]
-[knock on door]

25:35.242 --> 25:36.201
[sighs]

25:41.665 --> 25:43.250
This is not my house.

25:44.501 --> 25:45.752
What are you doing here?

25:46.586 --> 25:48.213
I just left my stag night.

25:48.296 --> 25:49.381
That doesn't help me.

25:50.090 --> 25:52.300
Your people call it a bachelor party.

25:53.468 --> 25:55.929
That would explain
the boob glitter on your face.

25:56.805 --> 25:59.099
Hmm… It got really weird.

25:59.182 --> 26:00.350
With the strippers?

26:00.934 --> 26:01.851
The mini horse.

26:03.311 --> 26:05.939
I don't even know
who to feel sorry for there.

26:12.362 --> 26:14.072
I can't get married tomorrow.

26:14.948 --> 26:15.865
[sighs]

26:17.367 --> 26:18.618
You should go home.

26:18.702 --> 26:19.744
I don't want to.

26:20.954 --> 26:22.330
Then go somewhere else.

26:25.250 --> 26:27.752
Can I, uh, just please come in?

26:27.836 --> 26:29.671
Find yourself a good therapist.

26:29.754 --> 26:30.672
-Please.
-No.

26:30.755 --> 26:32.882
-I really need to--
-Josh, you have to trust me.

26:32.966 --> 26:34.551
I think I'm gonna crap myself.

26:42.350 --> 26:43.226
It's…

26:44.394 --> 26:47.063
It's… around the corner.

26:47.605 --> 26:48.481
[Josh] Uh, okay.

26:50.317 --> 26:51.651
[indistinct chatter]

26:51.735 --> 26:53.320
[Beth] Oh, that's too much. Thank you.

26:53.403 --> 26:55.113
She'll tell you when you've had enough.

26:55.196 --> 26:56.614
-[woman 1] Mmm-hmm.
-[Beth chuckles]

26:56.698 --> 26:58.116
How do you know my uncle?

27:01.161 --> 27:03.705
-Just a work friend, bud.
-What does she do?

27:05.081 --> 27:05.957
Um…

27:06.750 --> 27:08.918
She helps me out. That right?

27:09.711 --> 27:10.712
We're partners.

27:12.839 --> 27:13.965
That all?

27:14.049 --> 27:15.258
[indistinct chatter]

27:21.222 --> 27:22.349
I'm married.

27:23.725 --> 27:25.143
How many children?

27:25.769 --> 27:26.603
Four.

27:27.187 --> 27:28.563
-She's married.
-Mmm-hmm.

27:28.646 --> 27:29.898
[woman 1 chuckles]

27:30.732 --> 27:31.733
Where's the ring?

27:34.819 --> 27:35.862
Let the girl eat.

27:35.945 --> 27:37.947
[laughs] Come on. I'm just playing.

27:38.573 --> 27:39.574
My cousin.

27:41.159 --> 27:42.202
Brother.

27:42.285 --> 27:43.286
Cousin.

27:48.958 --> 27:50.585
Heard a lot about you, Elizabeth.

27:51.878 --> 27:52.754
Just Beth.

27:53.630 --> 27:55.048
Okay, Elizabeth.

28:02.597 --> 28:03.973
Watch out for that one.

28:04.057 --> 28:05.809
[woman 2] Watch out for both these guys.

28:05.892 --> 28:08.228
-[all laughing]
-Like you're some peach.

28:08.311 --> 28:09.729
[all laughing]

28:11.981 --> 28:13.108
Is there a bathroom?

28:13.191 --> 28:14.901
-Inside, off the den.
-Thank you.

28:14.984 --> 28:16.027
[woman 2] Mmm-hmm.

28:20.907 --> 28:23.410
[door opens and closes]

28:26.871 --> 28:28.623
I'd avoid going in there.

28:29.374 --> 28:30.375
How long?

28:30.458 --> 28:32.085
A week, to be safe.

28:35.088 --> 28:36.840
-[sighs]
-Feeling better?

28:37.590 --> 28:38.675
Not really.

28:39.801 --> 28:40.635
Well…

28:41.177 --> 28:44.013
pre-wedding jitters are totally normal.

28:52.647 --> 28:54.858
I've never gone number two at Lila's.

28:57.026 --> 28:58.486
-Huh?
-Never.

28:59.529 --> 29:00.405
But…

29:00.989 --> 29:02.615
But what do you do?

29:03.199 --> 29:05.994
There's a cafe
down the street. They know me.

29:06.077 --> 29:07.787
The key's waiting when I come in.

29:07.871 --> 29:08.788
Why?

29:08.872 --> 29:12.500
Because her bathroom's so fresh
and girly. It smells like gardenias.

29:12.584 --> 29:15.044
Yeah, because she's
trying to mask her own dumps.

29:15.128 --> 29:16.337
Oh, she doesn't do that.

29:18.256 --> 29:20.842
So, she also goes to the cafe?

29:20.925 --> 29:22.802
No, she just doesn't do it.

29:22.886 --> 29:24.220
Are you kidding me?

29:24.304 --> 29:25.555
She never has to go.

29:26.139 --> 29:28.224
That's just physically impossible.

29:28.308 --> 29:30.935
She eats so clean,
there's very little waste.

29:34.189 --> 29:35.106
Jesus.

29:35.690 --> 29:36.608
Yeah.

29:38.443 --> 29:39.861
She really is perfect.

29:41.613 --> 29:42.822
Just not for me.

29:50.246 --> 29:53.917
You destroyed my office bathroom
after our first session.

29:54.626 --> 29:56.586
-[laughs] I thought I sprayed.
-Not enough.

29:56.669 --> 29:57.629
[chuckles]

30:08.348 --> 30:09.891
Can I ask you something?

30:11.226 --> 30:12.143
Okay.

30:14.187 --> 30:15.939
Do you really want to be with me?

30:19.108 --> 30:21.110
Or do you just not want to be with her?

30:27.116 --> 30:28.576
[sighs]

30:45.009 --> 30:46.719
["Whole Life" playing]

30:46.803 --> 30:53.309
♪ <i>Half of my own life is gone ♪</i>

31:02.360 --> 31:09.117
♪ <i>Let it drift and wash away ♪</i>

31:18.418 --> 31:24.924
<i>♪ It was just a dream ♪</i>

31:31.264 --> 31:32.891
-[Rio] What are you doing?
-[song stops]

31:37.186 --> 31:39.188
I don't… I don't know.

31:40.565 --> 31:42.734
Don't know? Don't want to say.

31:46.487 --> 31:48.740
[sighs] I'm just curious.

31:50.158 --> 31:51.117
Oh, yeah?

31:53.202 --> 31:54.537
You figure it out yet?

31:56.080 --> 31:57.165
What's that?

31:59.042 --> 32:00.585
Grandma loves Grisham.

32:01.252 --> 32:02.337
[both chuckle]

32:08.384 --> 32:09.427
[Beth clears throat]

32:10.637 --> 32:11.846
What is all this?

32:12.972 --> 32:13.973
[Rio] Family.

32:15.183 --> 32:16.726
Thought this was business.

32:19.020 --> 32:19.854
[Rio] Same thing.

32:23.566 --> 32:25.109
Why do they care about me?

32:26.235 --> 32:28.154
Got to know you're good enough.

32:31.240 --> 32:32.158
For you?

32:32.742 --> 32:33.785
For business.

32:37.121 --> 32:38.373
What if I'm not?

32:40.208 --> 32:42.001
Then you don't get invited back.

32:50.343 --> 32:52.303
-That doesn't seem fair.
-[scoffs]

33:12.573 --> 33:13.783
Mmm-mmm.

33:29.090 --> 33:30.717
[song resumes]

33:38.558 --> 33:45.314
♪ <i>Half of my whole life is done ♪</i>

33:52.905 --> 33:59.203
<i>♪ Heather gathers in its place ♪</i>

34:07.045 --> 34:13.676
<i>♪ It was just a dream I had ♪</i>

34:21.017 --> 34:25.897
<i>♪ It was just a dream ♪</i>

34:31.486 --> 34:34.614
<i>♪ The mark where he left me ♪</i>

34:34.697 --> 34:38.159
<i>♪ A clip on my wing ♪</i>

34:38.242 --> 34:41.412
<i>♪ Oh, let it soften ♪</i>

34:41.496 --> 34:44.999
<i>♪ I forgive everything ♪</i>

34:45.083 --> 34:48.836
<i>♪ I once hummed the seasons ♪</i>

34:52.840 --> 34:55.676
<i>♪ Now, I'm whistling ♪</i>

35:01.557 --> 35:02.600
What's going on?

35:05.686 --> 35:07.146
She improvised.

35:20.368 --> 35:21.327
Hey.

35:22.870 --> 35:23.871
They like you.

35:29.127 --> 35:30.461
[exhales]

35:46.644 --> 35:47.562
[grunts]

35:51.023 --> 35:51.899
Morning.

35:51.983 --> 35:54.527
-What time is it?
-You're good. You're good.

35:58.698 --> 35:59.615
But, uh…

36:01.576 --> 36:03.786
it's approaching go time.

36:03.870 --> 36:04.996
Oh, God.

36:12.336 --> 36:13.337
[clears throat]

36:20.469 --> 36:21.846
So what are you gonna do?

36:24.557 --> 36:26.267
Not how this works, remember?

36:27.852 --> 36:29.312
Oh, we're back to that now?

36:41.866 --> 36:43.576
You never really needed me.

36:55.296 --> 36:56.464
[sighs]

37:00.801 --> 37:01.719
Hi, Ben.

37:02.929 --> 37:04.889
You've got to be kidding me.

37:09.810 --> 37:12.104
Well, good luck.

37:12.188 --> 37:13.064
You, too.

37:13.940 --> 37:16.400
Hey. It's not that.

37:17.151 --> 37:18.778
Looks like that.

37:19.403 --> 37:21.948
It's… It's a different kind of that.

37:22.031 --> 37:23.532
That is that.

37:23.616 --> 37:27.161
[sighs] It's that without the that.

37:28.412 --> 37:31.207
Why should I believe
anything that comes out of your mouth?

37:31.290 --> 37:32.959
Because I'm not lying.

37:33.042 --> 37:35.253
I called the mini-mart after you left.

37:38.547 --> 37:39.465
What?

37:39.548 --> 37:40.633
Where were you?

37:42.385 --> 37:43.678
Not where you think.

37:43.761 --> 37:45.763
'Cause I think
you were humping your shrink.

37:45.846 --> 37:47.431
[scoffs] Jesus.

37:50.017 --> 37:52.812
I was at a GED prep class, okay?

37:56.148 --> 37:57.149
For real?

38:00.236 --> 38:01.070
Yeah.

38:05.658 --> 38:06.492
I just…

38:07.201 --> 38:08.744
I didn't want to tell you.

38:09.829 --> 38:10.997
Why?

38:12.331 --> 38:13.708
In case I failed again.

38:17.420 --> 38:18.337
How did you do?

38:21.966 --> 38:24.343
-[grunts]
-Come on, creeper in 4A.

38:24.427 --> 38:27.346
[grunts] He has really got to upgrade.

38:28.806 --> 38:30.016
It's loading.

38:30.641 --> 38:33.436
-Oh, my God. I can't look. I can't look.
-I got this.

38:34.103 --> 38:36.355
-[exhales sharply]
-[beeps]

38:37.523 --> 38:38.816
Oh, no.

38:44.196 --> 38:46.324
Now we both have to pay for college.

38:48.617 --> 38:50.119
[screams]

38:50.202 --> 38:51.620
[laughs]

38:53.247 --> 38:54.123
[Stan] Hey. [knocks]

38:54.790 --> 38:56.000
Rise and shine.

38:59.545 --> 39:01.505
-You just getting home?
-Mmm-hmm.

39:02.757 --> 39:03.883
Got my cut.

39:06.844 --> 39:07.762
For real?

39:08.596 --> 39:10.097
Did everything you said.

39:11.015 --> 39:11.974
How much?

39:12.058 --> 39:14.477
[scoffs] Even more than I asked for.

39:15.728 --> 39:16.645
How much?

39:18.647 --> 39:20.566
Depends on how many I sell.

39:23.110 --> 39:24.070
[Ruby] Why you?

39:25.446 --> 39:28.074
He didn't know any women
who could afford a real one.

39:29.241 --> 39:30.326
And we do?

39:32.078 --> 39:33.037
[sighs]

39:34.038 --> 39:35.539
We're gonna have to find them.

39:39.210 --> 39:40.628
Look legit, though.

39:41.962 --> 39:43.047
You see the hardware?

39:44.090 --> 39:45.007
[Ruby] Mmm-hmm.

39:47.343 --> 39:48.344
[Stan sighs]

39:49.095 --> 39:52.640
[character 1 on TV] <i>Sorry about this,</i>
<i>my gaily colored beach ball of rapture.</i>

39:52.723 --> 39:54.266
[character 2] <i>Actually, this look is…</i>

39:54.350 --> 39:56.894
Please turn that down.
You're gonna go deaf.

39:56.977 --> 39:58.604
[TV continues playing loudly]

39:58.687 --> 39:59.855
Dean?

40:00.815 --> 40:01.774
Earth to Dean?

40:06.028 --> 40:07.863
Oh, sorry. Just spaced.

40:08.697 --> 40:10.741
Weren't you gonna go on a bike ride?

40:11.534 --> 40:12.368
Can't.

40:13.202 --> 40:14.745
Didn't you fix the tires?

40:14.829 --> 40:15.871
[scoffs]

40:15.955 --> 40:18.374
I have a radius
of three blocks with this thing.

40:18.457 --> 40:21.293
Why don't you just go up
and down the driveway like Jane?

40:24.255 --> 40:26.215
-[TV continues playing loudly]
-It was a joke.

40:27.258 --> 40:28.884
You guys! TV.

40:30.886 --> 40:33.013
Might as well just throw me back in.

40:34.140 --> 40:36.183
Because you can't go on a bike ride?

40:36.267 --> 40:40.187
Because you gave them enough evidence
to put me away for as long as they want.

40:45.901 --> 40:47.945
I'll ask them to increase the radius.

40:48.028 --> 40:49.405
There's gonna be a trial.

40:49.488 --> 40:51.740
-There's not.
-They're not gonna cut me a deal.

40:51.824 --> 40:53.826
-You won't need one.
-How do you know that?

40:57.288 --> 40:58.998
Danny, turn the TV up.

41:00.833 --> 41:02.168
[raises volume]

41:02.251 --> 41:04.545
[on TV]<i> ♪ The soil he did crawl</i>
<i>Earthworm Jim… ♪</i>

41:04.628 --> 41:05.963
Come on. Even louder.

41:07.047 --> 41:08.507
[raises volume]

41:09.049 --> 41:10.468
<i>♪ But all that came to a crash… ♪</i>

41:10.551 --> 41:13.304
[mouthing] Because I made a deal
to get you out.

41:13.387 --> 41:15.764
<i>♪ He's such a groovy guy</i>
<i>Earthworm Jim ♪</i>

41:16.724 --> 41:17.600
[imperceptible]

41:17.683 --> 41:20.060
<i>♪ Cruising through the universe</i>
<i>Having lots of fun ♪</i>

41:20.144 --> 41:23.022
<i>♪ Here comes earthworm Jim</i>
<i>You know that he's a mighty one ♪</i>

41:26.901 --> 41:29.612
<i>♪ Earthworm Jim</i>
<i>A hero for all time ♪</i>

41:29.695 --> 41:32.656
<i>♪ Earthworm, Earthworm</i>
<i>Earthworm Jim ♪</i>

41:33.532 --> 41:36.494
<i>♪ Despite his great big muscles</i>
<i>And his really big ray gun ♪</i>

41:36.577 --> 41:38.996
<i>♪ Jim is still an earthworm</i>
<i>But then he's the only one ♪</i>

41:39.079 --> 41:41.916
<i>♪ With a super suit to make him</i>
<i>Really super strong ♪</i>

41:41.999 --> 41:44.627
<i>♪ Jim can be a winner</i>
<i>If we only sing along, all right! ♪</i>

41:44.710 --> 41:47.338
<i>♪ Earthworm Jim</i>
<i>We think he's mighty fine ♪</i>

41:47.421 --> 41:50.007
<i>♪ Earthworm Jim</i>
<i>A hero for all time ♪</i>

41:50.090 --> 41:52.843
<i>♪ Earthworm Jim</i>
<i>The soil he did crawl ♪</i>

41:52.927 --> 41:56.055
<i>♪ Earthworm, Earthworm</i>
<i>Earthworm, Earthworm Jim ♪</i>

41:56.138 --> 42:00.476
<i>♪ Hooray for Jim! ♪</i>

42:01.018 --> 42:02.603
<i>Groovy!</i>
